(besan),1 teaspoon Red Chilli powder,1/2 teaspoon Turmeric powder 
(Haldi),1 teaspoon Salt - to taste',10,35,45,4,'Maharashtrian Recipes','Lunch','Vegetarian','To begin making theÂ Khandeshi Dubuk Vade Recipe - Gram Flour Dumpling Curry, heat a kadai on medium heat, drizzle some oil.Â Add chopped onions and garlic and saute till it softens and the onions turn golden brown.Â Once the onions have lightly colored, add grated coconut and saute for 5 more minutes until the coconut have also roasted well.Â Add chopped coriander leaves and saute for 2 more minutes and turn off the heat.Allow the mixture to cool down for a while and then blitz it in a mixer with some water to a smooth and creamy mixture.Â To make the Dumpling / Kandeshi VadeMix besan flour, red chilli powder, turmeric powder and salt to taste. Add 1/4 cup water to it and mix to form a dropping consistency batter.Â Heat a kuzhi paniyaram pan on medium heat, drizzle some oil and drop in a spoonful of the batter into each cavity and allow the bhadi\'s to cook on either side for 5 minutes.Â Once done, take the fried Kandeshi Vade out and drain them over a paper napkin.Â To Make the Kandeshi Vade CurryÂ Heat a kadai on medium heat, drizzle some oil, add cumin seeds and allow it to crackle for few seconds.Add ground coriander and coconut paste and keep sauteing until the mixture reduces. Sprinkle all the spice powders like red chilli powder, turmeric powder, coriander powder, garam masala powder and salt to taste. Mix well.Â Add about 1 cup of water and and keep stirring until the Kandeshi Dubuk Vade Curry comes to a boil. Add in the fried Vade and allow the Kandeshi Dubuk Vade Curry to boil for 10 more minutes and turn off the heat.Â Check the salt and adjust the taste accordingly. Once done, transfer theÂ Khandeshi Dubuk Vade Recipe to a serving bowl and serve hot.Serve Khandeshi Dubuk Vade RecipeÂ - Gram Flour Dumpling CurryÂ along withÂ Jowar Atta Roti RecipeÂ andÂ Aloo Palak SabziÂ for your everyday simple Indian Lunch.','image4.jpg'),
(80,'Radish Soup Recipe','8 Mooli/ Mullangi 
