(Bengal Gram Dal),1 Raw Peanuts 
(Moongphali) - fistful,1 sprig Curry leaves,3 or 4 Green Chillies - finely chopped,1 teaspoon Ginger - grated,1 + 1 tablespoon Coconut Oil,Salt - to taste',30,30,60,4,'South Indian Recipes','Lunch','Vegetarian','To begin cooking the Thengai Sadam 
(Coconut Rice Recipe), heat a tablespoon of coconut oil in a heavy bottomed pan or wok.Â Add the mustard seeds to the oil, and once it begins to crackle, add in the urad dal, channa dal and the peanuts.Once theÂ dalsÂ begins to brown, add the green chillies, curry leaves and ginger and stir them together for a few minutes.Next, add in the coconut to theÂ kadaiÂ and mix them all together. Care should be taken to avoid any moisture remaining in the mixture,Â thereforeÂ keep stirring it properly until all the moisture inÂ the coconut evaporates. At this stage, stir in the cooked rice and salt and combine all the ingredients well.Â Add a tablespoon of coconut oil to it to separate the grains of the rice.Â Finally, add a tablespoon of coconut oil to the Thengai Sadam, to separate the grains of the rice.Â Stir fry gently to combine all the ingredient taking care and ensuring that the rice does not getÂ mashed,Â in the process. Once combined, turn the heat to low and simmer for a couple of minutes. Turn off the heat and serve the ThengaiÂ Sadam 
(Coconut Rice) hot with a potato roast and papad.','image10.jpg'),
(85,'Karwar Style Ambade Udid Methi Recipe - Hog Plum Curry','5 Hog Plum 
