(Haldi),3 cups Water,Salt - as needed',5,20,25,3,'South Indian Recipes','Lunch','Vegetarian','To begin making the Appalam Vatha Kuzhambu recipe, prepare all the ingredients and keep them ready.Heat oil in a preheated pan over medium heat. AddÂ mustard seeds, fenugreek seeds, curry leaves and dried red chilies. Allow it to crackle.Add the onions and saute until the onions have softened and lightly golden.Â Once the onions have softened, add the tamarind water, turmeric powder, sambar powder, jaggery and appalam.Add 3 cups of water, salt to taste and simmer the appalam vatha kuzhambu,Â until the kuzhambu has thickened and the appalam has soaked and cooked through as well.Â The Appalam Vatha Kuzhambu will have a gravy like consistency with the starch from the appalam giving it this texture. Adjust the consistency of the kuzhambu by adding water and also check the salt and spices and adjust to taste accordinglyServe the Appalam Vatha Kuzhambu along with hotÂ Steamed Rice,Â Bean Paruppu UsiliÂ andÂ Elai VadamÂ for simple and delicious weekend lunch.','image5.jpg'),
(110,'Kashmiri Style Modur Pulao With Pomegranate Recipe','1 cup Basmati rice - soaked for 1/2 hour,3 Cinnamon Stick 
