(Dhania) Leaves - for garnish',50,40,90,4,'Karnataka','Side Dish','Vegetarian','To begin making theÂ Brinjal Gravy For Biryani, first soak a lemon sized or 20 grams tamarind in hot water for 20 minutes.After 20 minutes extract the pulp of tamarind and keep aside. You will need 1/4 cup of tamarind pulp for this recipe.Â Add roughly chopped onions in a mixer and make an onion paste. Remove and keep it aside.Â In the same mixer, add the tomatoes and puree them. Keep aside.In a heavy bottomed pan,Â add 1 teaspoon of cooking oil. Let it warm up.Once the oil is hot, add the chopped brinjal till the skin becomes slightly brown. Once they are browned, remove from the pan and keep it aside. 
